

EARLIES

   The slang “earlies” is shorthand for “early adopters.” In the wake of
   the Bitcoin boom of 2017, the word “earlies” started being used to
   refer to early adopters of cryptocurrency, particularly of bitcoin.

   These early adopters are envied because they acquired their bitcoins
   when prices were still very slow. The Washington Post reported that
   $100 worth of Bitcoin in 2010 had acquired a value of $75 million by
   May 2017.

